frameDefinitions: A Mother and Father produce a Child or an Egg. 'Betty bore Gerry three intelligent daughters.'
A Sleeper transitions from a state of consciousness where they are largely unaware of their environment to a wakeful state.
The Creator creates a new entity, the Created_entity, possibly out of Components.
An Entity comes into existence at a particular Place and Time which may take a certain Duration_of_endstate, have a Cause, or be formed from Components.
An Agent changes the filler of a  Role by placing a New filler in the position after the Old filler ceases to occupy the position.
An Entity develops from a Prior_state to a Post_state.
frameExamples: The Libyans were <t>generating</t> arms for export.
Problems may <t>arise</t> whenever an S1 sophont enters the game.
If you <t>replace</t> me with a robot, who's gonna make excuses to your wife for you?
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Mother</fen> is the female creature that produces the <fen>Child</fen>.
<fen>Child</fen> identifies the new self-motile creature produced from the <fen>Mother</fen> and <fen>Father</fen>.
<fen>Father</fen> is the male creature that copulates with the <fen>Mother</fen>, thus  leading to the birth of the <fen>Child</fen>.
<fen>Egg</fen> is an immobile object containing an organism that may hatch as a mobile, infant organism.
The <fen>Mother</fen> and <fen>Father</fen> expressed together.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.
This role identifies the sleeping entity.
This describes the state out of which the <fen>Sleeper</fen> awakens.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.
The Creator creates a created entity.
This role identifies the entity that the Agent intentionally creates.
This role identifes the Time when an Agent intentionally creates a new entity.
This role identifies the place ehere the Agent intentionally creates the new entity.
Concrete or abstract entity that did not exist before the <fen>Time</fen> of the event.
This role identifes the Time when a new Entity comes into existence.
This is the Place where the new Entity comes into being.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs actions resulting in the <fen>New</fen> entity occupying the position.
The <fen>New</fen> entity is the person or thing that the <fen>Agent</fen> sets to fill a <fen>Role</fen>.
The entity that formerly occupied the position.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> installs the New entity.
This role identifies where the <fen>Agent</fen> installs the <fen>New</fen> entity.
The part of the <fen>Organism</fen> which is undergoing biological development.
The living thing whose <fen>Entity</fen> is undergoing development.
The relevant dimension of development.  Usually expressed by an entity-denoting adjective.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Entity</fen> develops.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> develops.
